  "commentary": "With SPX at 6591.85 sitting between the max negative gamma at 6580 (-13.27B) and max positive gamma at 6605 (+13.35B), dealers are currently in buy-mode as spot trades above the negative gamma concentration, creating upward pressure toward the 6605 resistance wall. The BREAKOUT regime with -32.6B total GEX means any directional move will be amplified by dealer hedging flows, particularly dangerous given the tight 25-point range between max negative/positive gamma levels. Watch 6580 as the critical support where dealer buying accelerates and 6605 as the key resistance where dealer selling kicks in - a break of either level should trigger violent moves given the regime.\n\nBottom line: expect wild swings between 6580 and 6605 with explosive moves if either level breaks.",
